---
// Garbage Disposal Repair, Same-Day Service Across Southern California
// BHGS #A49573 · BHGS #A49573

import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Garbage Disposal Repair, Same-Day Service Across Southern California";
const description = "Garbage disposal repair across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino & Riverside counties, jammed, humming, leaking, or not turning on. Appliance technicians (not plumbers). BHGS Licensed #A49573. EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410. $89 diagnostic, same day.";
const phone = MAIN_PHONE.display;
const phoneRaw = MAIN_PHONE.raw;
const phoneHref = MAIN_PHONE.href;
const schemaJsons = [
  JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "name": "Garbage Disposal Repair",
    "serviceType": "Garbage Disposal Repair",
    "description": "Garbage disposal repair across Southern California, jammed, humming, leaking, or not turning on. InSinkErator, Waste King, Moen, Badger, KitchenAid, Whirlpool, GE. Appliance technicians, not plumbers. BHGS Licensed #A49573. $89 diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "provider": {
      "@type": "LocalBusiness",
      "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair",
      "telephone": phone,
      "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/",
      "priceRange": "$$"
    },
    "areaServed": [
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"Los Angeles County"},
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"Orange County"},
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"Ventura County"},
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"San Bernardino County"},
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"Riverside County"}
    ],
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, applied toward the repair when approved" } }
  }),
  JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much does garbage disposal repair cost?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Our diagnostic fee is $89, and that gets applied to the repair the moment you approve the work. Most garbage disposal repairs run $120–$280 depending on the issue. A jam clearing or reset is on the lower end. Motor replacement or full unit swap is higher. We quote before we start, no surprises on the invoice."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which areas of Southern California do you cover for garbage disposal repair?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Same-day across Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties, West Hollywood, Silver Lake, and Culver City LA-side; Newport Beach, Anaheim, and Irvine OC; Thousand Oaks and Westlake Village in Ventura; Rancho Cucamonga and Riverside in the Inland Empire. Eight service territories total. InSinkErator, Waste King (Anaheim-local!), Moen, Badger, KitchenAid. BHGS Licensed #A49573."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "My garbage disposal is humming but not spinning, do I need a new one?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Not necessarily. Humming without spinning almost always means a jammed impeller plate, a foreign object or food buildup has locked the grinding mechanism. Our technicians clear the jam and test the motor before recommending replacement. In most cases, the unit is fine. We'll tell you honestly if it's not worth repairing."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why do you send an appliance technician instead of a plumber?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Most garbage disposal problems, jams, motor issues, electrical faults, worn seals, are appliance repairs, not plumbing work. A plumber's expertise is in pipes and drain lines. Our technicians specialize in the mechanical and electrical components of the disposal unit itself. If the issue turns out to be a drain line problem, we'll tell you that clearly."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can you repair my garbage disposal the same day?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes. We carry common InSinkErator, Moen, and Badger parts on the truck across all eight SoCal service territories. Call us and we'll give you an honest window for the same day. If we can't make it same day, we'll tell you exactly when, no vague 4-hour windows."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "My garbage disposal leaks under the sink, is it worth repairing?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "It depends on where the leak is coming from. A leak at the sink flange or drain connection is usually a seal replacement, straightforward and inexpensive. A crack in the housing of an older unit is a different story. Our technicians diagnose the source first, then give you a straight answer on repair vs. replacement."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What foods are hardest on garbage disposals in SoCal kitchens?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Southern California's food culture creates specific disposal issues. Avocado pits are the most common culprit we see, they're dense and will jam or crack the impeller plate. Artichoke leaves, fibrous citrus peel, and coffee grounds build up and cause chronic clogging. SoCal's hard water (300–400 mg/L TDS in LA, often higher in Inland Empire and parts of Riverside/San Bernardino on Colorado River supply) also accelerates mineral buildup inside the unit over time."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "When does it make sense to repair vs replace a garbage disposal?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Disposals last 8–12 years nationally, closer to the lower end across SoCal where hard water and heavy avocado/citrus use accelerate wear. Under 5 years old: repair almost always wins. 5–10 years with a jam, switch, or seal failure: repair. 10+ years with a motor failure on a 1/3 or 1/2 HP unit where motor replacement runs $180–$280 and a comparable new unit is $150–$250 plus install: we'll quote both and tell you directly. New 3/4 HP units run $200–$400; full installation labor is $120–$180. We give the honest math."
        }
      }
    ]
  }),
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">
    {schemaJsons.map((s) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={s}></script>
    ))}
  </Fragment>

  <style>
      :root {
        --red: #C8102E;
        --black: #0a0a0a;
        --gray: #f5f5f5;
        --border: #e2e2e2;
        --text: #1a1a1a;
        --muted: #6b6b6b;
        --white: #ffffff;
      }
      * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
      body { font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.6; }
      a { color: inherit; text-decoration: none; }
      img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }
  
      /* ── HERO ── */
      .hero {
        background: var(--black);
        color: #fff;
        padding: 80px 24px 72px;
      }
      .hero-inner {
        max-width: 1100px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 48px;
        align-items: center;
      }
      .hero-eyebrow {
        font-size: 13px;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: .12em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--red);
        margin-bottom: 16px;
      }
      .hero h1 {
        font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 46px);
        font-weight: 700;
        line-height: 1.15;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
        letter-spacing: -.02em;
        color: #fff;
      }
      .hero-sub {
        font-size: 17px;
        color: rgba(255,255,255,.72);
        margin-bottom: 32px;
        line-height: 1.6;
      }
      .hero-ctas { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
      .btn-primary {
        background: var(--red);
        color: #fff;
        padding: 14px 28px;
        border-radius: 6px;
        font-size: 15px;
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      .btn-outline {
        border: 1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,.35);
        color: #fff;
        padding: 14px 28px;
        border-radius: 6px;
        font-size: 15px;
        font-weight: 500;
      }
      .hero-rating {
        margin-top: 28px;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 10px;
        font-size: 13px;
        color: rgba(255,255,255,.55);
      }
      .stars { color: #f59e0b; letter-spacing: 2px; }
      .hero-img-wrap {
        border-radius: 12px;
        overflow: hidden;
        background: #1a1a1a;
        aspect-ratio: 4/3;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
      }
      .hero-img-placeholder {
        color: rgba(255,255,255,.2);
        font-size: 13px;
        text-align: center;
      }
  
      /* ── TRUST BAR ── */
      .trust-bar {
        background: var(--red);
        color: #fff;
        padding: 16px 24px;
      }
      .trust-bar-inner {
        max-width: 1100px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        display: flex;
        gap: 24px;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        justify-content: center;
      }
      .trust-item {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 8px;
        font-size: 13px;
        font-weight: 500;
      }
      .trust-icon { font-size: 16px; }
  
      /* ── SECTIONS ── */
      .section { padding: 72px 24px; }
      .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
      .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
      .container { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
      .section-label {
        font-size: 12px;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: .14em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--red);
        margin-bottom: 12px;
      }
      h2 {
        font-size: clamp(24px, 3.5vw, 36px);
        font-weight: 700;
        line-height: 1.2;
        letter-spacing: -.02em;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }
      .section-black h2 { color: #fff; }
      .lead {
        font-size: 17px;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: var(--muted);
        max-width: 680px;
        margin-bottom: 40px;
      }
      .section-black .lead { color: rgba(255,255,255,.65); }
  
      /* ── INTRO LAYOUT ── */
      .intro-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 340px;
        gap: 48px;
        align-items: start;
      }
      .intro-text p { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 18px; }
      .intro-text p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  
      /* Tip block */
      .tip {
        background: #fff8e7;
        border: 1px solid #f0d070;
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 18px 20px;
        margin-top: 28px;
      }
      .tip-label { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: .1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #b08000; margin-bottom: 8px; }
      .tip p { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: #6b5800; }
  
      /* Sticky CTA box */
      .cta-box {
        background: var(--black);
        color: #fff;
        border-radius: 12px;
        padding: 28px 24px;
        position: sticky;
        top: 24px;
      }
      .cta-box h3 { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 8px; }
      .cta-box p { font-size: 14px; color: rgba(255,255,255,.65); margin-bottom: 20px; }
      .cta-phone {
        display: block;
        background: var(--red);
        color: #fff;
        text-align: center;
        padding: 14px;
        border-radius: 6px;
        font-size: 16px;
        font-weight: 700;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }
      .cta-book {
        display: block;
        border: 1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,.25);
        color: #fff;
        text-align: center;
        padding: 12px;
        border-radius: 6px;
        font-size: 14px;
      }
      .cta-note { font-size: 12px; color: rgba(255,255,255,.4); text-align: center; margin-top: 12px; }
      .pricing-mini { margin-top: 20px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.1); padding-top: 16px; }
      .pricing-mini-item { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; font-size: 13px; padding: 5px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.07); }
      .pricing-mini-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
      .pricing-mini-label { color: rgba(255,255,255,.55); }
      .pricing-mini-val { font-weight: 600; color: #fff; }
  
      /* ── PROBLEMS GRID ── */
      .problems-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
        gap: 20px;
        margin-top: 40px;
      }
      .problem-card {
        background: #fff;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 10px;
        padding: 24px;
      }
      .problem-icon { font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
      .problem-card h3 { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 8px; }
      .problem-card p { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--muted); }
  
      /* ── LA CONTEXT ── */
      .context-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 40px;
        align-items: center;
      }
      .context-text p { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: rgba(255,255,255,.75); margin-bottom: 16px; }
      .context-text p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
      .context-facts { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; }
      .fact-card {
        background: rgba(255,255,255,.06);
        border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.1);
        border-radius: 10px;
        padding: 20px;
      }
      .fact-card h4 { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 6px; color: #fff; }
      .fact-card p { font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.6; color: rgba(255,255,255,.55); }
  
      /* ── DIFFERENTIATOR ── */
      .diff-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 24px;
        margin-top: 40px;
      }
      .diff-card {
        border-radius: 10px;
        padding: 24px;
      }
      .diff-card.them {
        background: #fdf2f2;
        border: 1px solid #f5c6c6;
      }
      .diff-card.us {
        background: #f0faf0;
        border: 1px solid #90d090;
      }
      .diff-card h3 { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 14px; }
      .diff-card.them h3 { color: #c02020; }
      .diff-card.us h3 { color: #207020; }
      .diff-list { list-style: none; }
      .diff-list li { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; padding: 5px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.06); color: var(--muted); }
      .diff-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
      .diff-list li::before { margin-right: 8px; }
      .diff-card.them .diff-list li::before { content: "✗"; color: #c02020; }
      .diff-card.us .diff-list li::before { content: "✓"; color: #207020; }
  
      /* ── RECENT REPAIRS ── */
      .repairs-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr));
        gap: 20px;
        margin-top: 40px;
      }
      .repair-card {
        background: #fff;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 10px;
        padding: 22px;
      }
      .repair-tag {
        display: inline-block;
        background: var(--gray);
        font-size: 11px;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: .08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--muted);
        padding: 3px 8px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        margin-bottom: 12px;
      }
      .repair-card h3 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 10px; line-height: 1.3; }
      .repair-card p { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--muted); }
  
      /* ── WHY US ── */
      .why-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr));
        gap: 20px;
        margin-top: 40px;
      }
      .why-card {
        background: #fff;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 10px;
        padding: 24px;
      }
      .why-icon { font-size: 26px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
      .why-card h3 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 8px; }
      .why-card p { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--muted); }
  
      /* ── REVIEWS ── */
      .reviews-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 20px;
        margin-top: 40px;
      }
      .review-card {
        background: #fff;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 10px;
        padding: 22px;
      }
      .review-stars { color: #f59e0b; font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
      .review-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 14px; font-style: italic; }
      .review-author { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text); }
      .review-location { font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); }
  
      /* ── PRICING ── */
      .pricing-table {
        width: 100%;
        border-collapse: collapse;
        margin-top: 32px;
        font-size: 15px;
      }
      .pricing-table th {
        text-align: left;
        padding: 12px 16px;
        background: var(--black);
        color: #fff;
        font-size: 13px;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: .05em;
      }
      .pricing-table td {
        padding: 14px 16px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        color: var(--text);
      }
      .pricing-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
      .pricing-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--gray); }
      .price-range { font-weight: 700; color: var(--red); }
      .pricing-note {
        font-size: 13px;
        color: var(--muted);
        margin-top: 16px;
        padding: 14px 16px;
        background: var(--gray);
        border-radius: 6px;
        border-left: 3px solid var(--red);
      }
  
      /* ── FAQ ── */
      .faq-list { margin-top: 40px; }
      .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px 0; }
      .faq-item:first-child { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
      .faq-q { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 10px; }
      .faq-a { font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); }
  
      /* ── NEARBY ── */
      .nearby-grid {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 10px;
        margin-top: 28px;
      }
      .nearby-link {
        background: var(--gray);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 6px;
        padding: 8px 14px;
        font-size: 14px;
        color: var(--text);
        transition: border-color .15s;
      }
      .nearby-link:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }
  
      /* ── BOTTOM CTA ── */
      .bottom-cta {
        background: var(--black);
        color: #fff;
        padding: 72px 24px;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .bottom-cta h2 { margin-bottom: 16px; color: #fff; }
      .bottom-cta p { font-size: 17px; color: rgba(255,255,255,.65); margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 520px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; }
      .bottom-ctas { display: flex; gap: 12px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  
      @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .hero-inner, .intro-grid, .context-grid, .diff-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
        .hero-img-wrap { display: none; }
        .reviews-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
        .intro-grid { gap: 32px; }
      }
    </style>

<!-- ── HERO ── -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <p class="hero-eyebrow">LA · Orange · Ventura · San Bernardino · Riverside Counties</p>
      <h1>Garbage Disposal Repair Across Southern California</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Jammed, humming, leaking, or not turning on, our appliance technicians diagnose and fix it same day across LA, OC, Ventura & the Inland Empire. We carry parts for InSinkErator, Moen, Badger, and Waste King (Anaheim-local!) on the truck.</p>
      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href={phoneHref} class="btn-primary">☎ {phone}</a>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn-outline">Book Online</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-img-wrap">
      <div class="hero-img-placeholder">
        <p>Garbage Disposal Repair</p>
        <p>Across Southern California</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── TRUST BAR ── -->
<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">🏅</span> BHGS Licensed #A49573</div>
    <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">🛡️</span> Fully Insured</div>
    <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">⚡</span> Same Day Available</div>
    <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">🔩</span> OEM Parts on Truck</div>
    <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">💬</span> $89 Diagnostic, Waived With Repair</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ── INTRO ── -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="intro-grid">
      <div class="intro-text">
        <p class="section-label">Appliance Repair Specialists</p>
        <h2>Most garbage disposal calls don't need a plumber</h2>
        <p>We get a lot of calls from people who've already spent money on a plumber that couldn't fix the problem, or who were quoted a full replacement when the disposal had years of life left in it. Here's the thing: most garbage disposal issues are appliance problems, not plumbing problems. Jammed impellers, failed motors, worn seals, electrical faults, that's appliance territory.</p>
        <p>Our technicians work on garbage disposals the same way they work on every other kitchen appliance: they diagnose the actual problem, explain what it is, and give you a straight answer on whether it's worth repairing. We carry InSinkErator, Moen, and Badger parts on the truck for most calls across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties, and Waste King, with its Anaheim, CA factory just minutes from our OC service area. If your drain line has a problem, that's when you call a plumber. We'll tell you if that's the case.</p>
        <p>SoCal's food culture creates some specific issues we see constantly. Avocado pits are the most common culprit across SoCal kitchens, they're dense enough to crack an impeller plate on contact. Artichoke leaves, fibrous citrus peel, and coffee grounds build up and cause chronic clogging in open floor plan kitchens where the disposal runs hard every day. Southern California's hard water, 300–400 mg/L TDS in LA, often higher in the Inland Empire and parts of Riverside/San Bernardino on Colorado River supply, accelerates mineral buildup inside the unit faster than most people realize.</p>

        <div class="tip">
          <div class="tip-label">⚠️ Before you call anyone, try this first</div>
          <p>Press the red reset button on the bottom of the disposal. It's a small rubber button, most jams trip a thermal overload switch that cuts power. If it's popped out, press it in and try the disposal again. If it trips again immediately, there's a real problem. If pressing reset doesn't help and you can hear humming, the impeller plate is jammed. Don't keep running it, you'll burn out the motor. Call us.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cta-box">
        <h3>Same Day Garbage Disposal Repair</h3>
        <p>Call now for availability in your area across Southern California.</p>
        <a href={phoneHref} class="cta-phone">☎ {phone}</a>
        <a href="/contact/" class="cta-book">Book Online</a>
        <p class="cta-note">BHGS Licensed #A49573 · Insured · No call center</p>
